to the editor the rights of gay americans editorial march 27 tells the story of thomas mclaughlin a 14 year old who has been harassed by his school because he is gay my heart goes out to him although much progress has been made in the struggle for gay rights since 1959 when in my final semester of college i was expelled because of a gay relationship with another student the fight for dignity and equal protection under the law continues my wish is that the young mr mclaughlin suffer none of the confusion and self loathing i experienced then that the fear irrationality and ignorance of those dark ages should still be manifest in the laws of texas and elsewhere is a continuing travesty in our so called free and equal society peter coffeen norfolk conn march 27 2003

